On Wednesday evening, iHub at Bishop Magua Centre, Ngong road, hosted TED Fellows to a networking cocktail. The team had just has completed a tour of the region. During the event, there were brief talks from the fellows about their experiences and what it takes to be a TED fellow on the global scale. It ended with the commencement announcement of the 2017 TED Global Fellowship application process. In attendance were Amref regional manager Dr Liz Wala, BRCK Ushahidi co-founder Juliana Rotich and scientist Manjala Mlagui.